# Docusaurus Project Structure

This project follows the standard Docusaurus structure with TypeScript support for the Don't Starve Together API documentation.

## Key Files

- [docusaurus.config.ts](mdc:dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/docusaurus.config.ts) - Main configuration file
- [sidebars.ts](mdc:dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/sidebars.ts) - Sidebar navigation structure
- [package.json](mdc:dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration

## Core Directories

- `/docs` - Documentation markdown files
  - `/api-vanilla` - API documentation organized by module categories
  
- `/src` - Source code
  - `/pages` - React components for custom pages
  - `/components` - Reusable React components
  - `/css` - Custom CSS files

- `/static` - Static assets
  - `/img` - Images including logo and favicon
  - [404.html](mdc:dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/dst-api-webdocs/static/404.html) - Custom 404 page

## Development Workflow

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start development server
npm start

# Build the site
npm run build

# Test the production build locally
npm run serve

# Deploy to GitHub Pages
npm run deploy
```

## TypeScript Usage

The project uses TypeScript for enhanced type safety:
- React components use `.tsx` extension
- Configuration files use `.ts` extension
- Type definitions are provided by Docusaurus packages

